Whereas, for the application of the provisions in Article 28 (3) of the sixth Directive, paragraph 2 (aa) of Annex IX (Taxation) to the Act of Accession of the Kingdom of Sweden to the European Communities (3), authorizes Sweden to exempt certain transactions listed in Annex F to the sixth Directive;
Whereas Sweden is unable to make a precise calculation of the VAT own resources base for certain categories of transactions listed in Annex F, point 2 to the sixth Directive, whereas such calculation is likely to involve an unjustified administrative burden in relation to the effect of these transactions on Sweden's total VAT resources base; whereas Sweden should therefore be authorized not to take these transactions into account for the calculation of the VAT base;
Whereas Sweden is able to make a calculation using approximate estimates for four categories of transactions listed in Annex F to the sixth Directive; whereas Sweden should therefore be authorized to calculate the VAT base using approximate estimates;
Whereas the Advisory Committee on Own Resources has approved the report recording the opinions of its members on this Decision,

